originalText.text: Terrible experience, i have an auto loan with pen fed and although the dealership I purchased the vehicle dropped the ball on the title pens fed has done little to assist. Their customer service department is not educated and has advised me on 2 separate occasions to go to the dmv when they cannot assist me since pen fed has to pay them directly. Then all they needed to do is email me paper work to get this situated but it’s been over 2 weeks and I couldn’t even get that. When I asked if anything can be done for my inconvenience they told me no. So you can give people misinformation, drags your feet in the process and it is as if them wasting my time energy and money was for no reason. I would not recommend this company to anyone.

originalText.text: I have an auto loan through Penfed and it's been nothing but lies and hassles with Penfed lately. They are extremely unhelpful and the customer care associates can be quite rude. If you fall on hard times or experience a major life event such as loss of a job, they don't care. They say they will help you but they don't. They do not even communicate with you. Trying to talk to an actual person is like an act of god because they just bounce you from one rep to the next and nobody knows the truth. I will be refinancing my vehicle asap so that I no longer have to deal with Penfed as I am sick of their outright lying.
